Comment.val: /*Function to update the register for Reijnders transactions.*/

Text.val: Used to create a lock for the internal transfer without locking the transaction itself:
Class 50 is present when TR_TRANS_MUNTS has a value (always present for transfers):
Check if the party side of the transaction is already processed :
To prevent multiple execution of the counterparty side (by sending the same message twice) also check if it's already processed:
Storno transactions will not be processed (yet).
Create register if it's not an internal transfer or the party side is not processed :
For YTD (Revaluation in case of succession) register as receiving
If it's a TRANSFER_IN_SECURITIES ('D') from the portfolioconversion (OriginCode='PCBM') then the
participations will be added via the export function triggered by the TRANSFER_OUT_SECURITIES with OriginCode='PCBM'.
In an Internal transfer there is no calculation of Reynderstax. Only the register records involved in the
transfer must be copied from the party to the counterparty. So NAV and TIS aren't meaningfull thus not added:
Only for Product conversions from Market securities to BG funds (Transfer_In_Securities = BG fund) use the first quote known
